This article is a statement by George Shultz, William Perry, Henry Kissinger, and Sam Nunn regarding the United Nations Security Council meeting on nuclear nonproliferation and nuclear disarmament. The statement emphasizes the importance of global focus on the risks posed by the spread of nuclear weapons, know-how, and material. The authors express their commitment to reducing reliance on nuclear weapons, preventing their spread, and ultimately eliminating them as a threat to the world. They also commend the leadership of the U.S. administration in this effort. The article mentions that these individuals have previously co-authored op-eds in The Wall Street Journal on the topic of nuclear disarmament.